article.headline: Rose layup forces OT, but Bucks' Mason takes over thereafter
article.linkText: Raptors bow to Bucks in OT, go 4-6 without VC
article.story:
TORONTO (AP) -- Desmond Mason had 23 points and Michael Redd scored 10 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Toronto Raptors 107-105 in overtime on Friday night Jalen Rose sent the game overtime with a driving layup at the buzzer, but Mason had five points in the extra period and Toronto's Morris Peterson missed a potential tying jumper with one second left. Maurice Williams added 22 points for the Bucks, who have won just three of their 15 road games. Rose and Eric Williams each had 21 points for the Raptors, who are 4-6 since trading Vince Carter to New Jersey on Dec. 17. Redd went 2-for-13 from the field in the first three quarters before his jumper and three-point play gave Milwaukee a 85-84 lead with 4:35 left -- the Bucks' first lead since the first half. Redd's two free throws made it 95-91 with 15 seconds remaining, but Donyell Marshall made a 3-pointer and Mason missed the first of two free throws to give Toronto a chance to tie with six seconds left. Rose followed with his driving layup. Peterson's 3-pointer cut Milwaukee's to two with 2:00 left in overtime, but the Raptors followed that by missing three straight 3-point attempts. Mason made two throws to make it a four-point game with 22 seconds left before Rose converted a three-point play to cut it to one with 15 seconds remaining in overtime. Mason made one of two free throws before Peterson missed his running jumper.

Game notes
Toronto coach Sam Mitchell was an assistant to Milwaukee coach Terry Porter two years ago. ... The Raptors collected donations to help tsunami victims during the game. Rose donated $1,000 for every point he scored. ... The Raptors went 1-for-5 from behind the 3-point arc in the extra period.
